# [DETNET](../wg/detnet.html)

## Summary

The DETNET Working Group met at IETF 126. The session was co-chaired by János Farkas and Lou Berger, with Yves Schuler serving as secretary. The meeting covered working group status, updates on adopted data plane and control plane documents, and several new individual proposals.

Key highlights included:
* Announcement of two newly published RFCs from the RAW (Reliable and Available Wireless) work: RAW Technologies and RAW Architecture.
* Discussion on coordinating with ITU-T Study Group 13 regarding deterministic networking progress and a formal liaison received for action on stateless fair queuing.
* Technical updates on taxonomy, latency guarantees, deadline-based forwarding, timeslot queuing, on-time forwarding, multi-domain control plane frameworks, and SRv6 service protection.
* Presentation of new proposals covering flow aggregation, jitter control from policing, traffic deviation handling, and PREOF observability.

