## Decisions and Action Items
* **Liaison Response to ITU-T SG13**: The working group will draft a response to the ITU-T SG13 action liaison regarding the progress of deterministic networking and `draft-ietf-detnet-stateless-fair-queuing`. Lou Berger invited interested participants to contribute to the response drafting on the mailing list.
* **ITU-T Coordination**: Authors of `draft-ietf-detnet-stateless-fair-queuing` must work to ensure total alignment of the metadata fields (e.g., the transition from 3 to 4 fields) and ensure no text duplication with the ITU-T specifications. John Scudder (AD) and Lou Berger emphasized that any duplicates must be resolved while the draft is in the working group, prior to IESG review.

